/* ==========================================
=02. MEMBER GROUP COLORS
GROUP COLOR SYSTEM (Legacy Compatible)
==========================================

VARIABLE NAMING:
--ac1 Hex color for primary accent (e.g., #b50600)
--ac1r RGB triplet for primary (e.g., 181, 6, 0) - use with rgba()
--ac2 Hex color for secondary accent
--ac2r RGB triplet for secondary
--gbg1 Same as ac1r (for Lover theme compatibility)
--gbg2 Same as ac2r (for Lover theme compatibility)
--gbg3 Blended color (average of ac1r and ac2r)

USAGE EXAMPLES:
color: var(--ac1); → Hex color
color: rgb(var(--ac1r)); → RGB color
background: rgba(var(--gbg1), 0.5); → With opacity
background: linear-gradient(rgb(var(--gbg1)), rgb(var(--gbg2)));

SELECTORS:
.group-X Class selector (applied to .pr-wrap in post_row.html)
#g-X Legacy ID selector for general pages
#p-X Legacy ID selector for profile/post pages

TO ADD A NEW GROUP:
1. Copy an existing group block
2. Change the group number in selectors
3. Update the hex values (--ac1, --ac2)
4. Update the RGB triplets (--ac1r, --ac2r)
5. Calculate --gbg3 as average of the two RGB values
6. Add corresponding #g-X and #p-X selectors below
7. Optionally add a gradient text class

COLOR REFERENCE (by group):
┌────────┬──────────────┬─────────────────┬─────────────────┐
│ Group │ Name │ ac1 (primary) │ ac2 (secondary) │
├────────┼──────────────┼─────────────────┼─────────────────┤
│ 1-3 │ Default │ #4BA9EB blue │ #F1D432 gold │
│ 4 │ Admin │ #b50600 red │ #d7b137 gold │
│ 6 │ Red │ #ED3B4D │ #ba4646 │
│ 7 │ Orange │ #c15c00 │ #BA6621 │
│ 8 │ Yellow │ #D1A802 │ #D9BF5E │
│ 9 │ Green │ #1EA881 │ #77BA90 │
│ 10 │ Blue │ #3481E0 │ #4BA9EB │
│ 11 │ Purple │ #8773E6 │ #9682FF │
│ 12 │ Corrupted │ #9d74ff │ #8eea5d │
│ 13 │ Pastel │ #ccaefa │ #ffb5db │
│ 14 │ Pink │ #f24991 │ #EB6F9A │
│ 15 │ Neutral │ #7C80A3 │ #8286AB │
└────────┴──────────────┴─────────────────┴─────────────────┘

========================================== */

/* =======================================
BANNER FROSTED GLASS (GIF-safe)

Replaces backdrop-filter with filter:blur() on pseudo-elements.
backdrop-filter re-samples its backdrop every compositor frame;
animated GIFs on the same layer force continuous re-blurs, causing
visible twitching in Chrome.

::before = blurred copy of the banner image (background-attachment:
fixed keeps it aligned with the real banner regardless of position).
::after = glass tint overlay (replaces the element's old background).
======================================= */

.twai-box::before,
.banner-welcome::before,
.banner-staff::before,
.banner-updates::before,
.staff-bio::before {
content: "";
position: absolute;
inset: -40px;
background: var(--banner-pic);
background-size: cover;
background-position: center;
background-attachment: fixed;
z-index: -2;
}

.twai-box::before { filter: blur(12px); }
.banner-welcome::before,
.banner-staff::before,
.banner-updates::before { filter: blur(16px); }
.staff-bio::before { filter: blur(20px); }

.twai-box::after {
content: "";
position: absolute;
inset: 0;
background: rgba(200, 30, 45, 0.4);
z-index: -1;
}

.banner-welcome::after,
.banner-staff::after,
.banner-updates::after,
.staff-bio::after {
content: "";
position: absolute;
inset: 0;
background: var(--glass-bg-strong);
z-index: -1;
}

/* ===============
FORUM ROW - COMIC PANELS
Frosted glass aesthetic with 4-panel layout
=============== */

/* ==========================================
FORUM ROW: Glass variables scoped to last poster's group
The group class (e.g. .group-14) on .lover-alt-fr sets --gbg1/2/3
We re-declare glass variables here using the forum row's color variables
========================================== */

.lover-alt-fr[class*="group-"] {
--glass-bg:
linear-gradient(rgba(var(--gbg3), var(--glass-tint-opacity)), rgba(var(--gbg3), var(--glass-tint-opacity))),
linear-gradient(var(--glass-bg-base), var(--glass-bg-base));
--glass-bg-strong:
linear-gradient(rgba(var(--gbg3), var(--glass-tint-opacity)), rgba(var(--gbg3), var(--glass-tint-opacity))),
linear-gradient(var(--glass-bg-strong-base), var(--glass-bg-strong-base));
}

This forces CSS variable inheritance to work correctly */

/* From css_animations.css - heartbeat animation (lowercase variant) */
@-webkit-keyframes heartbeat {

10% { -webkit-transform: scale(0.91); transform: scale(0.91); -webkit-animation-timing-function: ease-in; animation-timing-function: ease-in; }
17% { -webkit-transform: scale(0.98); transform: scale(0.98); -webkit-animation-timing-function: ease-out; animation-timing-function: ease-out; }
33% { -webkit-transform: scale(0.87); transform: scale(0.87); -webkit-animation-timing-function: ease-in; animation-timing-function: ease-in; }
45% { -webkit-transform: scale(1); transform: scale(1); -webkit-animation-timing-function: ease-out; animation-timing-function: ease-out; }
}
@keyframes heartbeat {
from { transform: scale(1); transform-origin: center center; animation-timing-function: ease-out; }
10% { transform: scale(0.91); animation-timing-function: ease-in; }
17% { transform: scale(0.98); animation-timing-function: ease-out; }
33% { transform: scale(0.87); animation-timing-function: ease-in; }
45% { transform: scale(1); animation-timing-function: ease-out; }
}

/* Avatar ring pulse animation */

70% { box-shadow: 0 0 0 15px rgba(var(--gbg1), 0); }
100% { box-shadow: 0 0 0 0 rgba(var(--gbg1), 0); }
}

/* Avatar orbit rotation animation */

100% { transform: rotate(360deg); }
}

/* ===============================================
POST ROW & MINI PROFILE - Glass Morphism Design
===============================================

TEMPLATE FILES:
- templates/post_row.html → Main post structure
- templates/mini_profile.html → Sidebar profile card

STRUCTURE OVERVIEW:
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ .pr-wrap │
│ ├── .pr-date (date bar) │
│ └── .pr-glass (main container) │
│ └── .pr-layout (flex row) │
│ ├── .pr-sidebar-col (320px column) │
│ │ ├── .pr-sidebar (sticky profile) │
│ │ │ ├── .pr-portrait │
│ │ │ └── .pr-content │
│ │ │ ├── .pr-name │
│ │ │ ├── .pr-subtitle │
│ │ │ ├── .pr-divider │
│ │ │ ├── .pr-species │
│ │ │ ├── .pr-faceclaim │
│ │ │ ├── .pr-stats │
│ │ │ └── .pr-badge │
│ │ └── .pr-user-links (bottom, fixed) │
│ └── .pr-main (flex column) │
│ ├── .pr-body (post content) │
│ └── .pr-footer │
│ ├── .pr-ooc │
│ └── .pr-post-actions │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

COLOR VARIABLES USED:
- rgb(var(--gbg1)) → Primary accent color
- rgb(var(--gbg2)) → Secondary accent color
- rgb(var(--gbg3)) → Tertiary accent color
- var(--glass-bg) → Glass background
- var(--glass-border) → Glass border color
- var(--text) → Text color
- var(--bg2) → Secondary background

=============================================== */

/* =======================================
BACKDROP-FILTER FIX (Per-element)

These properties on ANCESTORS break backdrop-filter:
- contain: paint
- filter (any)
- transform (any)
- will-change

Apply fixes to ancestor chain of each element that needs blur.
======================================= */

#Profile .lover-body-contain {
background: transparent;
}

#Profile #innerwrapper,
#Profile .tableborder,
#Profile .profile-app,

filter: none !important;

}

/* =============================================
PROFILE HERO SECTION
CSS Grid layout with fixed aspect ratios

GRID STRUCTURE:
┌─────────────┬───────┬──────────┐
│ │ sq-top│ │
│ rect ├───────┤ portrait │
│ 16:10 │ sq-bot│ 10:16 │
└─────────────┴───────┴──────────┘
============================================= */

.profile-hero {
display: flex;
flex-direction: column;
width: 100%;
}

/* All profile sections share same width and centering */
.profile-hero-images,
.profile-hero-info,
.profile-body {
width: 100%;
max-width: 1100px;
margin-left: auto;
margin-right: auto;
box-sizing: border-box;
}

/* IMAGE GRID - Responsive with proportional columns

Column proportions (from aspect ratios):
- rect (16:10): 64 parts
- squares (1:1): 20 parts
- portrait (10:16): 25 parts

Container aspect-ratio: (64+20+25) : 40 ≈ 109:40
This maintains all internal ratios at any width.
*/
.profile-hero-images {
display: grid;
grid-template-columns: 64fr 20fr 25fr;
grid-template-rows: 1fr 1fr;
gap: 4px;
aspect-ratio: 109 / 40;
width: 100%;
max-width: 1100px;
border-radius: 16px 16px 0 0;
overflow: hidden;
border: 1px solid var(--glass-border);
border-bottom: none;
background: var(--glass-bg);
backdrop-filter: blur(8px);
-webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(8px);
}

.profile-hero-img {
background-size: cover;
background-position: center;
min-width: 0;
min-height: 0;
}

/* RECT: spans both rows */
.hero-rect {
grid-column: 1;
grid-row: 1 / 3;
}

/* SQUARES: one per row */
.hero-sq-top {
grid-column: 2;
grid-row: 1;
}

.hero-sq-bot {
grid-column: 2;
grid-row: 2;
}

/* PORTRAIT: spans both rows */
.hero-portrait {
grid-column: 3;
grid-row: 1 / 3;
}

<script>
/* WatcherAPI — thin client for The Watcher (jcink_crawler)
* Inlined in wrapper.html <head>. No dependencies.
* See API_CONTRACT.md for endpoint docs.
*/
var WatcherAPI = (function() {
var meta = document.querySelector('meta[name="watcher-api"]');
var BASE_URL = meta ? meta.getAttribute('content') : 'https://imagehut.ch:8943';

function fetchJSON(path) {
return fetch(BASE_URL + path).then(function(r) {
if (!r.ok) throw new Error('WatcherAPI ' + r.status + ': ' + path);
return r.json();
});
}

return {
BASE_URL: BASE_URL,
getCharacters: function() { return fetchJSON('/api/characters'); },
getClaims: function() { return fetchJSON('/api/claims'); },
getFields: function(ids, fields) {
var q = '?ids=' + ids.join(',');
if (fields && fields.length) q += '&fields=' + fields.join(',');
return fetchJSON('/api/characters/fields' + q);
},
getCharacter: function(id) { return fetchJSON('/api/character/' + id); },
getCharacterThreads: function(id) { return fetchJSON('/api/character/' + id + '/threads'); },
getThreadCounts: function(id) { return fetchJSON('/api/character/' + id + '/thread-counts'); },
getCharacterQuote: function(id) { return fetchJSON('/api/character/' + id + '/quote'); },
getCharacterQuotes: function(id) { return fetchJSON('/api/character/' + id + '/quotes'); },
sendActivity: function(event, opts) {
var body = { event: event };
if (opts) {
if (opts.thread_id) body.thread_id = opts.thread_id;
if (opts.forum_id) body.forum_id = opts.forum_id;
if (opts.user_id) body.user_id = opts.user_id;
}
navigator.sendBeacon(
BASE_URL + '/api/webhook/activity',
new Blob([JSON.stringify(body)], { type: 'application/json' })
);
}
};
})();
</script>
</head>

<script>

function read_alerts() {
$('#recent-alerts').slideToggle('slow');
$.get( "index.php?recent_alerts=1&read=1", function( data ) {
$( "#recent_alerts_data" ).html( data );
});
$( ".alerts-indicator" ).html( "Alerts (0)");
}


function load_alerts() {

alert_link = $('.alerts-indicator').position().left-350;
$('#recent-alerts').css({
left: alert_link + "px",
});
if($('#recent-alerts').is(':visible')) {
$('#recent-alerts').slideToggle('slow');
} else {
$.get( "index.php?recent_alerts=1", function( data ) {
$( "#recent-alerts-data" ).html( data );
});
$("#recent-alerts").slideToggle('slow');
}
}
</script>

<!-- Tab Navigation -->

<div class="profile-tab-nav">
<label for="ptab-1"><i class="las la-fire-alt"></i> Abilities</label>
<label for="ptab-2"><i class="las la-book"></i> Biography</label>
<label for="ptab-3"><i class="las la-link"></i> Plotting</label>
<label for="ptab-4"><i class="las la-list"></i> Threads</label>

<!-- Tab 1: Abilities -->
<div class="profile-tab-panel" id="panel-1">
<h3>Abilities</h3>
Superhuman Strength:<br />
The woman is STRONG. Capable of lifting vehicles and yeeting them when people annoy her with relative ease, she is definitely a powerhouse of a woman.<br />
<br />
Superhuman Durability:<br />
Alright, so she's not bulletproof - even if she tells people otherwise just so they won't shoot her. She is, however, just built different. She can withstand a large amount of blunt force, and although she is not entirely invulnerable by any means she does also have a regenerative healing factor that allows her to heal more quickly than most humans.<br />
<br />
Street Smarts:<br />
Jess may not be a genius of the Tony Stark variety, but she is an incredibly PI. She sees patterns, notices things that other people may not, and is very good at reading people. It may be easy to think of the angry drunk as "a dumb broad" as she's been called, but she's anything but that.

<h3>Weaknesses</h3>
PTSD:<br />
Diagnosed with PTSD and a handful of other issues thanks to her upbringing with Dorothy Walker and her time with Killgrave, Jessica has PTSD that present as untimely flashbacks, inability to differentiate real memories from false memories without time and effort, and a series of nightmares. The flashbacks can be debilitating in a fight if they come at a bad time, and have been in the past.<br />
<br />
Alcoholism:<br />
A full blown alcoholic, Jessica is highly reliant on abusing liquor to cope with life and deal with people. It would be incredibly unhealthy, if she didn't have a regenerative healing factor - which is, of course, the excuse she uses to keep doing it. She can get drunk with large amounts of alcohol, but it does little damage to her organs. Just, y'know, makes her a drunk.<br />
<br />
Call Declined:<br />
Jessica Jones claims not to answer the call of heroism. She's not a hero. She's just an asshole that can lift heavy shit. Nick Fury? Bitch buttoned. Abigail Brand? Bitch buttoned. She's not going to put on a spandex suit and fight crime, she's going to do it in her normal street clothes like a respectable person and pretend that she's not fighting the good fight so that people leave her alone. (She also helps lead an underground resistance but never mind that).
</div>

<!-- Tab 2: Biography -->
<div class="profile-tab-panel" id="panel-2">
<b>THE INTERVIEW</b><br />
<br />
For starters, I'd like to say this isn't an interview. It might as well be an interrogation, you fuckers black bagged me and flew me all the fuck the way out to the middle of nowhere, claiming it's for your safety and mine. I have a phone, you know. Or an email account, if you're old school. A bar that I frequent that you could've talked to me at.<br />
<br />
Anyway. I'm not entirely sure why SHIELD is interested in me, but I can take a few guesses. I'm a super person, I'm a PI that's probably as good at getting information as some of their precious spies. I just don't murder people for the information. I've got a pretty large network to work with, which I'm guessing is the real reason, because you already seem to know that. Not entirely sure how I landed the misfortune of an underground revolution at my back, but here we are.<br />
<br />
Well, I guess it's not too underground if you know about us. I'm not even the only person in charge there, you know. And all three of the others would be a hell of a lot more pleasant to deal with than I am. But you picked your poison. Sucks to suck.<br />
<br />
I can give you about a hundred reasons why you shouldn't want to work with me. For starters, everyone knows I'm a drunk. I don't like being told what to do, and don't follow orders. I don't like tradition, if there's a better way to get shit done I'm gonna do it and I'm not asking anybody's permission. I don't want to be a hero, I just want innocent people to not have to live in hiding because of some shitty assholes who decided that all super people are the problem. Fury seems like the kind of guy who demands respect, and I don't like commands - or respect. And finally, I'm really not the biggest fan of the Avengers. We'll call it a 'difference of opinion'.<br />
<br />
You kill people. I don't. I know, it's for the greater good and sometimes it's necessary. Only, with what I do? It's not necessary. We've found ways around it. I respect what you do, but if I do what you do I have to compromise the only slice of a moral that I have left. Not gonna happen.<br />
<br />
The ugly truth is that I've done it before. But you know that. I didn't have a choice - literally, there was a man worming his way into my mind and every aspect of my existence, taking over. But you know that too. So you aren't too surprised by the fact that I'm not willing to play dolls with the people who own the house and make all the dolls themselves.<br />
<br />
If you want to know more about Kilgrave, just google it. It's old news. Dude took a liking to me. I'm not gonna go into everything that entails, you're not getting horror porn here, but I'll say that he used me to do his dirty work, and there's blood on my hands. I'm not adding more to it.<br />
<br />
That's all I'm saying. The news and police reports were very detailed if you want the ugly stuff. Figure shit out yourself. But you want an Ally? Well, maybe we can work something out if you pony up a drink or two.<br />
<br />
<b>THE NEGOTIATION</b><br />
<br />
I think the misunderstanding here is whether or not I want to help people. I do, just not the way that you do. I don't want to save the world, I just want to save my city. The city you ripped me out of for this stupid little discussion. Not that I'm really gunning for the destruction of the rest of the world, but I can't help them. New York City, though? Hell's Kitchen? If there was anyone I considered 'my people', which is a bit of a stretch, it'd be them.<br />
<br />
So, I'm willing to negotiate a little. I'm not a SHIELD agent and that's never gonna happen, and I'm sure as fuck not gonna be an Avenger. But you supply me and my little resistance with tech and equipment? I'll do some mercenary jobs for you. I'll try to get my people to contract for you if the job is up their alley. We've got a lot of useful information, and we get more every day. We're not writing up a contract here, but we can have a symbiotic relationship. You need us, we need you.<br />
<br />
That's my offer. Take it or leave it, I genuinely could not force myself to give a shit if I tried. Now take me home.
</div>

<!-- Tab 3: Plotting -->
<div class="profile-tab-panel" id="panel-3">
<h3>Platonic</h3>
There are two sides to Jessica's friendship. On one hand, she's a terrible friend. She'll be rude, push you away, go for the throat if she feels like you're getting a bit too close for comfort. She'll ignore your texts and calls, sometimes even ridicule you. On the other hand, she may not be there for the little stuff but you can be damn sure she'll be there for the big stuff. She may be rough around the edges and generally a toxic person to have in your life, and she may claim not to care about people (a lie), but Jessica Jones would put her life on the line for almost every single person she knows, and most people she doesn't know. She's a shockingly good leader, and despite what she says it's fairly easy to see that she genuinely cares about people.

<h3>Romantic</h3>
To put it bluntly, Jessica is a 'hit it and quit it' type of girl. Bar bathroom hookups, one night stands, anything that gives her a physical distraction without bordering on an emotional one is her style. That said, if she ever were to consider someone for more than a night or two, it would be someone who can bite back when she gets venemous and keep up with her, who doesn't push her to be someone that she's not but can appreciate her for the trainwreck that she is, and someone who can go toe-to-toe against enemies - even if that enemy is admittedly sometimes herself.

<h3>Antagonistic</h3>
There are a great number of people who could be considered enemies of Jessica. People who, despite all the evidence and known super people in the world, believe that she used fake mind control as an excuse to do terrible things. People who she's picked fights with in the past or was just generally shitty to. Past flings that may have gotten a little too attached and were pushed away a little too roughly. And, of course, AIM. While Jessica isn't very public about what she does, she and the other Defenders have no doubt been leaked as leaders of an underground rebellion. It can't be proven, or at least it hasn't been yet, but if they got her alone and it wouldn't make a public mess? She'd be shot on sight.

<h3>Plot Hooks</h3>
SHIELD: Jessica is more of a hired hand for SHIELD, rather than an official agent. She works with them on specific cases that happen to be up her alley, and is openly defiant of command. I'd love for her to interact with anyone involved with SHIELD, whether it's someone who's begrudgingly involved or someone who genuinely believes in the values of SHIELD so that she can begin to see that as well.<br />
<br />
THE REBELLION: Jessica and the Defenders are the leader of the local rebels in New York City, with their base being in Hell's Kitchen. She's not exactly the recruiter, she's far too rough around the edges for that, but she handles intel and organization. Got a local rebel you want to get involved? She's your gal.<br />
<br />
SUPER SOLDIERS: I genuinely just want Jessica to meet the other super soldiers. She isn't quite one of them, but the experiments to make her stronger and more durable were essentially a wish.com knockoff of the super soldier serum and basically, I want her to find out and pout about the fact that she got the shitty version.<br />
<br />
OTHER SUPERS: Right now, Jess isn't exactly a huge fan of the Avengers. She doesn't blame them, but she doesn't trust them either. In the comics, she definitely works with them a bit (even joining them at one point) and I'd love to see some action there that could potentially change her mind about them.<br />
<br />
DRINKING BUDDIES: Honestly, this is the most casual friendship I can think of and we could definitely talk about it leading to other types of plots, whether it's antagonistic or not. Joining the rebels, finding out they're on opposite sides, etc.<br />
<br />
EXES: I'm not gonna lie, I love that Jessica Jones isn't really prim and proper, particularly when it comes to sex. I'd love to have scorned ex flings, ex flings that still have some hope that she can snuff out, exes turned to friends/enemies/etc., all of it.
</div>

/******************************
DYNAMIC HEADER HEIGHT
Measures top-nav and header-nav
to set banner height dynamically
*******************************/
function setHeaderHeights() {
var topNav = document.querySelector('.lover-top-nav');
var headerNav = document.querySelector('.header-nav');
var banner = document.querySelector('.header-banner');

if (topNav && headerNav && banner) {
var topNavHeight = topNav.offsetHeight;
var headerNavHeight = headerNav.offsetHeight;
banner.style.setProperty('--top-nav-height', topNavHeight + 'px');
banner.style.setProperty('--header-nav-height', headerNavHeight + 'px');
}
}

document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', setHeaderHeights);
window.addEventListener('resize', setHeaderHeights);

/******************************
APPLY STAR-TAB CLASS
Adds .star-tab to categories
listed in tabbedCategories
*******************************/
document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function() {
if (window.tabbedCategories && window.tabbedCategories.length) {
window.tabbedCategories.forEach(function(catId) {
var cat = document.querySelector('.cat-' + catId);
if (cat) {
cat.classList.add('star-tab');
initStarTab(cat);
}
});
}
});

function initStarTab(cat) {
var tableborder = cat.closest('.tableborder');
var prevBtn = tableborder ? tableborder.querySelector('.star-prev') : null;
var nextBtn = tableborder ? tableborder.querySelector('.star-next') : null;
var currentPage = 1;

function getCardsPerRow() {
var slide = cat.querySelector('.star-page-2 .lover-rc-slide');
if (!slide) return 4;
var containerWidth = slide.offsetWidth;
var gap = 25;
var minCardWidth = 200;
var maxCardWidth = 350;
// Calculate how many cards fit, favoring wider cards
var cardsPerRow = Math.max(1, Math.floor((containerWidth + gap) / (minCardWidth + gap)));
// Cap at reasonable max
cardsPerRow = Math.min(cardsPerRow, 6);
console.log('Star-tab: container=' + containerWidth + 'px, cards per row=' + cardsPerRow);
return cardsPerRow;
}

function redistributeCards() {
// Collect all cards from all pages
var allCards = [];
cat.querySelectorAll('.star-page .lover-rc-slide').forEach(function(slide) {
slide.querySelectorAll('.lover-alt-fr').forEach(function(card) {
// Skip the hidden placeholder (first child of page 2)
if (!card.classList.contains('star-placeholder')) {
allCards.push(card);
}
});
});

// Remove any dynamically created pages (3, 4, etc.)
cat.querySelectorAll('.star-page-3, .star-page-4, .star-page-5').forEach(function(page) {
page.remove();
});

var page2Slide = cat.querySelector('.star-page-2 .lover-rc-slide');
if (!page2Slide) return;

// Mark the hidden placeholder
var firstChild = page2Slide.querySelector('.lover-alt-fr:first-child');
if (firstChild) firstChild.classList.add('star-placeholder');

var cardsPerRow = getCardsPerRow();
// Filter out placeholder
var visibleCards = allCards.filter(function(c) { return !c.classList.contains('star-placeholder'); });

console.log('Star-tab: ' + visibleCards.length + ' visible cards, ' + cardsPerRow + ' per row');

// Put first batch in page 2
visibleCards.slice(0, cardsPerRow).forEach(function(card) {
page2Slide.appendChild(card);
});

// Create additional pages for overflow
var remaining = visibleCards.slice(cardsPerRow);
var pageNum = 3;
var lastPage = cat.querySelector('.star-page-2');

while (remaining.length > 0) {
var newPage = document.createElement('div');
newPage.className = 'star-page star-page-' + pageNum;
var newSlide = document.createElement('div');
newSlide.className = 'lover-rc-slide';
newPage.appendChild(newSlide);
lastPage.after(newPage);

remaining.slice(0, cardsPerRow).forEach(function(card) {
newSlide.appendChild(card);
});

console.log('Star-tab: Created page ' + pageNum + ' with ' + Math.min(cardsPerRow, remaining.length) + ' cards');
remaining = remaining.slice(cardsPerRow);
lastPage = newPage;
pageNum++;
}

return pageNum - 1; // Total pages (including page 1 guidebook)
}

function getTotalPages() {
var pages = cat.querySelectorAll('.star-page');
return pages.length;
}

function updatePageState() {
var totalPages = getTotalPages();
// Update at-last-page class
if (currentPage >= totalPages) {
cat.classList.add('at-last-page');
} else {
cat.classList.remove('at-last-page');
}
console.log('Star-tab: Page ' + currentPage + '/' + totalPages);
}

function goToPage(page) {
var totalPages = getTotalPages();
if (page < 1) page = 1;
if (page > totalPages) page = totalPages;
currentPage = page;

// Remove all page classes
cat.classList.remove('show-forums', 'show-page-3', 'show-page-4', 'show-page-5');

// Apply appropriate classes (specific page only, not cumulative)
if (currentPage >= 2) cat.classList.add('show-forums');
if (currentPage === 3) cat.classList.add('show-page-3');
else if (currentPage === 4) cat.classList.add('show-page-4');
else if (currentPage === 5) cat.classList.add('show-page-5');

updatePageState();
}

// Initial setup
redistributeCards();
updatePageState();

// Button handlers
if (prevBtn) {
prevBtn.addEventListener('click', function() {
console.log('Star-tab: Prev clicked');
goToPage(currentPage - 1);
});
}

if (nextBtn) {
nextBtn.addEventListener('click', function() {
console.log('Star-tab: Next clicked');
goToPage(currentPage + 1);
});
}

// Recalculate on resize (debounced)
var resizeTimeout;
window.addEventListener('resize', function() {
clearTimeout(resizeTimeout);
resizeTimeout = setTimeout(function() {
var wasOnPage = currentPage;
redistributeCards();
var totalPages = getTotalPages();
// Stay on same page if possible, else go to last page
goToPage(Math.min(wasOnPage, totalPages));
}, 150);
});
}

/******************************
STAR BUTTON SPARKLE BURST
Creates sparkles that burst
from the chevron center
Triggers when button scrolls into view
*******************************/
document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function() {
var sparkleChars = ['✦', '✧', '⋆', '✶', '✷', '★', '☆'];
var hasTriggered = false;

// Only get the FIRST visible .star-next button (the one on first category load)
var firstNextBtn = document.querySelector('.star-nav .star-next');
if (!firstNextBtn) return;

var icon = firstNextBtn.querySelector('i, .material-icons');
if (!icon) return;

// Use IntersectionObserver to trigger when button comes into view
var observer = new IntersectionObserver(function(entries) {
entries.forEach(function(entry) {
if (entry.isIntersecting && !hasTriggered) {
hasTriggered = true;
observer.disconnect();
// Small delay after becoming visible
setTimeout(function() {
createSparkleBurst(icon);
}, 200);
}
});
}, { threshold: 0.5 });

observer.observe(firstNextBtn);

function createSparkleBurst(icon) {
var numSparkles = 18;
var iconRect = icon.getBoundingClientRect();

// Center point in viewport coordinates (fixed position)
var centerX = iconRect.left + iconRect.width / 2;
var centerY = iconRect.top + iconRect.height / 2;

for (var i = 0; i < numSparkles; i++) {
var sparkle = document.createElement('span');
sparkle.className = 'star-sparkle';
sparkle.textContent = sparkleChars[Math.floor(Math.random() * sparkleChars.length)];

// Fully random angle - no pattern
var angle = Math.random() * Math.PI * 2;
// More varied distance range
var distance = 50 + Math.random() * 150;

// Calculate end position
var tx = Math.cos(angle) * distance;
var ty = Math.sin(angle) * distance;

// More varied sizes
var size = 8 + Math.random() * 18;

// Random delay instead of sequential
var delay = Math.random() * 0.4;
// More varied duration
var duration = 0.6 + Math.random() * 0.8;

// Fixed position on body - no clipping
sparkle.style.cssText =
'position: fixed;' +
'left: ' + centerX + 'px;' +
'top: ' + centerY + 'px;' +
'font-size: ' + size + 'px;' +
'z-index: 99999;' +
'--tx: ' + tx + 'px;' +
'--ty: ' + ty + 'px;' +
'--delay: ' + delay + 's;' +
'--duration: ' + duration + 's;';

// Append to body so they're not clipped
document.body.appendChild(sparkle);

// Remove sparkle after animation
setTimeout(function(s) {
return function() { s.remove(); };
}(sparkle), 2500);
}
}
});

/******************************
SUBFORUM DISPLAY
Star-tab: inline pill buttons in card-content
Regular: flyout menu from caption-box trigger
*******************************/
document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function() {
document.querySelectorAll('.lover-alt-fr').forEach(function(card) {
var subforumsDiv = card.querySelector('.subforums');
if (!subforumsDiv) return;

// Extract subforum data from <a> links OR <select> options
var subforumData = [];
var links = subforumsDiv.querySelectorAll('a:not(.subforums-macro)');
if (links.length > 0) {
links.forEach(function(link) {
subforumData.push({ href: link.href, text: link.textContent.trim(), title: link.title || '' });
});
} else {
var selectEl = subforumsDiv.querySelector('select');
if (selectEl) {
var options = selectEl.querySelectorAll('option');
options.forEach(function(opt) {
if (opt.value && opt.value !== '' && opt.value !== '0' && opt.textContent.trim() !== '') {
subforumData.push({ href: opt.value, text: opt.textContent.trim(), title: '' });
}
});
}
}

if (subforumData.length === 0) return;

// Check if this card is inside a star-tab category
var isStarTab = !!card.closest('.star-tab');

if (isStarTab) {
// Star-tab mode: put subforum links as pill buttons in card-content
var cardContent = card.querySelector('.card-content');
if (!cardContent) return;

var btnContainer = document.createElement('div');
btnContainer.className = 'subforum-buttons';

subforumData.forEach(function(sf) {
var btn = document.createElement('a');
btn.href = sf.href;
btn.className = 'subforum-btn';
btn.textContent = sf.text;
btn.title = sf.title;
btnContainer.appendChild(btn);
});

// Insert after title, before last-post info
var lastPost = cardContent.querySelector('.card-last-post');
if (lastPost) {
cardContent.insertBefore(btnContainer, lastPost);
} else {
var statsDiv = cardContent.querySelector('.card-stats');
if (statsDiv) {
cardContent.insertBefore(btnContainer, statsDiv);
} else {
cardContent.appendChild(btnContainer);
}
}
} else {
// Regular mode: flyout from caption-box trigger
var captionBox = card.querySelector('.caption-box');
if (!captionBox) return;

var trigger = document.createElement('button');
trigger.className = 'subforum-trigger';
trigger.innerHTML = '<i class="material-icons globe-icon">public</i><i class="material-icons flight-icon">flight</i>';
trigger.title = 'Locations';

var flyout = document.createElement('div');
flyout.className = 'subforum-flyout';

subforumData.forEach(function(sf) {
var btn = document.createElement('a');
btn.href = sf.href;
btn.className = 'subforum-btn';
btn.textContent = sf.text;
btn.title = sf.title;
flyout.appendChild(btn);
});

trigger.addEventListener('click', function(e) {
e.stopPropagation();
flyout.classList.toggle('open');
});

document.addEventListener('click', function() {
flyout.classList.remove('open');
});

captionBox.appendChild(trigger);
card.appendChild(flyout);
}
});
});

// Shrink top nav after scrolling past banner
(function() {
const topNav = document.querySelector('.lover-top-nav');
const banner = document.querySelector('.header-banner');
const pulse = document.querySelector('.lover-top-nav pulse');

if (topNav && banner) {
window.addEventListener('scroll', function() {
const bannerBottom = banner.getBoundingClientRect().bottom;
if (bannerBottom <= 0) {
topNav.classList.add('shrunk');
} else {
topNav.classList.remove('shrunk');
}
});
}

// Custom dropdown for character select
if (pulse) {
let customDropdown = null;

pulse.addEventListener('click', function(e) {
e.preventDefault();
e.stopPropagation();

// Remove existing dropdown
if (customDropdown) {
customDropdown.remove();
customDropdown = null;
return;
}

const select = document.querySelector('#subaccounts_menu select, #subaccounts_menu .forminput');
if (!select || !select.options) return;

// Build custom dropdown
customDropdown = document.createElement('div');
customDropdown.className = 'avatar-dropdown';

Array.from(select.options).forEach(function(opt) {
const item = document.createElement('div');
item.className = 'avatar-dropdown-item';
item.textContent = opt.textContent;
item.dataset.value = opt.value;
if (opt.selected) item.classList.add('selected');

item.addEventListener('click', function() {
select.value = opt.value;
select.form.submit();
});

customDropdown.appendChild(item);
});

// Append to body to escape backdrop-filter stacking context
document.body.appendChild(customDropdown);

// Position based on pulse location
const rect = pulse.getBoundingClientRect();
customDropdown.style.position = 'fixed';
customDropdown.style.left = rect.left + 'px';
customDropdown.style.top = rect.bottom + 5 + 'px';
});

// Close dropdown when clicking outside
document.addEventListener('click', function(e) {
if (customDropdown && !pulse.contains(e.target) && !customDropdown.contains(e.target)) {
customDropdown.remove();
customDropdown = null;
}
});
}
})();

// Staff bio modal
(function() {
const banner = document.querySelector('.header-banner');
const avatars = document.querySelectorAll('.staff-avatar');
const bios = document.querySelectorAll('.staff-bio');
const closeBtns = document.querySelectorAll('.staff-bio-close');

if (!banner || !avatars.length) return;

function openBio(staffId) {
// Hide other panels
banner.classList.add('staff-modal-open');

// Clear previous active states
avatars.forEach(a => a.classList.remove('active'));
bios.forEach(b => b.classList.remove('active'));

// Set new active states
const avatar = document.querySelector('.staff-avatar[data-staff="' + staffId + '"]');
const bio = document.querySelector('.staff-bio[data-for="' + staffId + '"]');
if (avatar) avatar.classList.add('active');
if (bio) bio.classList.add('active');
}

function closeBio() {
banner.classList.remove('staff-modal-open');
avatars.forEach(a => a.classList.remove('active'));
bios.forEach(b => b.classList.remove('active'));
}

// Click handlers for avatars
avatars.forEach(function(avatar) {
avatar.addEventListener('click', function(e) {
e.preventDefault();
const staffId = this.dataset.staff;
if (this.classList.contains('active')) {
closeBio();
} else {
openBio(staffId);
}
});
});

// Close button handlers
closeBtns.forEach(function(btn) {
btn.addEventListener('click', function(e) {
e.preventDefault();
e.stopPropagation();
closeBio();
});
});
})();

// Populate staff character grids from WatcherAPI
// Uses alias from /api/claims + square_image from getFields
(function() {
var grids = document.querySelectorAll('.staff-characters[data-staff-alias]');
if (!grids.length || typeof WatcherAPI === 'undefined') return;

WatcherAPI.getClaims().then(function(claims) {
if (!claims.length) return;

// Batch-fetch square_image for all characters (alias comes from claims directly)
var allIds = claims.map(function(c) { return c.id; });
WatcherAPI.getFields(allIds, ['square_image']).then(function(fields) {

// Build lookup: id → { name, profile_url, alias, square_image }
var byId = {};
claims.forEach(function(c) {
var f = fields[c.id] || {};
byId[c.id] = {
id: c.id,
name: c.name,
profile_url: c.profile_url,
alias: (c.alias || '').trim(),
square_image: f.square_image || ''
};
});

grids.forEach(function(grid) {
var staffAlias = grid.getAttribute('data-staff-alias');
if (!staffAlias) return;
var aliasLower = staffAlias.toLowerCase().trim();

// Filter by alias from claims data
var chars = Object.values(byId).filter(function(c) {
return c.alias && c.alias.toLowerCase() === aliasLower;
}).sort(function(a, b) {
return a.name.localeCompare(b.name);
});

if (!chars.length) {
var aliases = [...new Set(Object.values(byId).map(function(c) { return c.alias; }).filter(Boolean))].sort();
console.log('[Staff] No characters for "' + staffAlias + '". Available aliases:', aliases);
return;
}
console.log('[Staff] Found ' + chars.length + ' characters for "' + staffAlias + '"');

chars.forEach(function(c) {
var img = c.square_image;
if (!img) return;

var a = document.createElement('a');
a.href = c.profile_url;
a.title = c.name;

var imgEl = document.createElement('img');
imgEl.src = img;
imgEl.alt = c.name;

a.appendChild(imgEl);
grid.appendChild(a);
});
});

}).catch(function(err) { console.log('[Staff] getFields failed:', err); });
}).catch(function(err) { console.log('[Staff] getClaims failed:', err); });
})();

// Guidebook tabs
(function() {
document.querySelectorAll('.gb-tabs').forEach(function(tabContainer) {
var tabs = tabContainer.querySelectorAll('.gb-tab');
var panel = tabContainer.closest('.guidebook-panel-left');
if (!panel) return;
var panes = panel.querySelectorAll('.gb-pane');

tabs.forEach(function(tab) {
tab.addEventListener('click', function(e) {
e.preventDefault();
var targetId = this.getAttribute('href').substring(1);
var targetPane = panel.querySelector('#' + targetId);

// Update active states
tabs.forEach(function(t) { t.classList.remove('active'); });
panes.forEach(function(p) { p.classList.remove('active'); });

this.classList.add('active');
if (targetPane) targetPane.classList.add('active');
});
});
});
})();

// Characters Panel (API-powered via WatcherAPI, cached in localStorage)
(function() {
var FALLBACK_IMG = 'https://placehold.co/150x200/1a1a1a/666?text=?';
var ROTATE_INTERVAL = 30000;
var FADE_DURATION = 400;
var CACHE_KEY = 'twaitheme_characters';
var CACHE_MAX_AGE = 5 * 60 * 1000; // 5 minutes
var currentRandomIndices = {};

// Map API group_name to CSS group class number
var GROUP_NAME_MAP = {
'admin':4, 'red':6, 'orange':7, 'yellow':8, 'green':9,
'blue':10, 'purple':11, 'corrupted':12, 'pastel':13, 'pink':14, 'neutral':15
};

// Save only the fields we need to keep cache small
function toCache(members) {
return members.map(function(m) {
return { id: m.id, name: m.name, square_image: m.square_image || m.avatar_url || '', profile_url: m.profile_url, group_name: m.group_name };
});
}

function saveCache(members) {
try {
localStorage.setItem(CACHE_KEY, JSON.stringify({ ts: Date.now(), data: toCache(members) }));
} catch (e) { /* quota exceeded, ignore */ }
}

function loadCache() {
try {
var raw = localStorage.getItem(CACHE_KEY);
if (!raw) return null;
var cached = JSON.parse(raw);
// Return data regardless of age (for instant render), but flag staleness
cached.stale = (Date.now() - cached.ts) > CACHE_MAX_AGE;
return cached;
} catch (e) { return null; }
}

function populateCards(members, container, fade) {
var cards = container.querySelectorAll('.character-card');
for (var i = 0; i < cards.length && i < members.length; i++) {
var member = members[i];
var card = cards[i];
var portrait = card.querySelector('.card-portrait');
var name = card.querySelector('.card-name');

if (fade) {
card.style.opacity = '0';
card.style.transition = 'opacity ' + FADE_DURATION + 'ms ease';
}

portrait.style.backgroundImage = 'url(' + (member.square_image || member.avatar_url || FALLBACK_IMG) + ')';
name.textContent = member.name;
card.style.cursor = 'pointer';

var gid = member.group_name ? GROUP_NAME_MAP[member.group_name.toLowerCase()] : null;
card.className = 'character-card' + (gid ? ' group-' + gid : '');

(function(url) {
card.onclick = function() { window.location.href = url; };
})(member.profile_url);

if (fade) {
(function(c) {
requestAnimationFrame(function() { c.style.opacity = '1'; });
})(card);
}
}
}

function fadeOutCards(container) {
return new Promise(function(resolve) {
var cards = container.querySelectorAll('.character-card');
cards.forEach(function(card) {
card.style.transition = 'opacity ' + FADE_DURATION + 'ms ease';
card.style.opacity = '0';
});
setTimeout(resolve, FADE_DURATION);
});
}

function shuffle(arr) {
for (var i = arr.length - 1; i > 0; i--) {
var j = Math.floor(Math.random() * (i + 1));
var tmp = arr[i]; arr[i] = arr[j]; arr[j] = tmp;
}
return arr;
}

function pickRandom(allMembers, count) {
var pool = allMembers.slice(3);
var available = [];
for (var i = 0; i < pool.length; i++) {
if (!currentRandomIndices[i]) available.push(i);
}
if (available.length < count) {
currentRandomIndices = {};
for (var i = 0; i < pool.length; i++) available.push(i);
}
var picked = shuffle(available).slice(0, count);
currentRandomIndices = {};
picked.forEach(function(i) { currentRandomIndices[i] = true; });
return picked.map(function(i) { return pool[i]; });
}

// Filter and sort raw API data into display-ready list
function prepareMembers(raw) {
var filtered = raw.filter(function(m) {
if (!m.group_name || !GROUP_NAME_MAP[m.group_name.toLowerCase()]) return false;
var name = (m.name || '').toLowerCase().trim();
var alias = (m.alias || '').toLowerCase().trim();
if (name.indexOf('watcher') !== -1 || alias.indexOf('watcher') !== -1) return false;
return true;
});
filtered.sort(function(a, b) { return parseInt(b.id) - parseInt(a.id); });
return filtered;
}

// Wire up the panel: populate cards + start rotation
function initPanel(allMembers, newSection, randomSection) {
if (!allMembers.length) return;
populateCards(allMembers.slice(0, 3), newSection);
populateCards(pickRandom(allMembers, 3), randomSection);

if (allMembers.length > 6) {
setInterval(function() {
fadeOutCards(randomSection).then(function() {
populateCards(pickRandom(allMembers, 3), randomSection, true);
});
}, ROTATE_INTERVAL);
}
}

document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function() {
var panel = document.querySelector('.characters-panel');
if (!panel) return;
var newSection = panel.querySelector('.characters-section:first-child .character-cards');
var randomSection = panel.querySelector('.characters-section:last-child .character-cards');
if (!newSection || !randomSection) return;

var cached = loadCache();
var usedCache = false;

// Instant render from cache if available
if (cached && cached.data && cached.data.length) {
var cachedMembers = prepareMembers(cached.data);
if (cachedMembers.length) {
initPanel(cachedMembers, newSection, randomSection);
usedCache = true;
}
}

// Always fetch fresh data in background
WatcherAPI.getCharacters().then(function(raw) {
if (!raw || !raw.length) return;
var freshMembers = prepareMembers(raw);
if (!freshMembers.length) return;

// Update cache (toCache maps avatar_url → square_image internally)
saveCache(freshMembers);

// If we already rendered from cache, silently update "New" cards
// (random rotation handles itself via the interval)
if (usedCache) {
populateCards(freshMembers.slice(0, 3), newSection);
} else {
initPanel(freshMembers, newSection, randomSection);
}
}).catch(function(err) {
console.log('[CharPanel] API error:', err);
// If no cache was used and API failed, cards stay as placeholders
});
});
})();</script>

<!-- Panel-3: Fetch last poster's portrait from Watcher API (Field 7) -->
<script>
document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function() {
var forumRows = document.querySelectorAll('.lover-alt-fr');
if (!forumRows.length) return;

// Collect unique poster IDs and map rows by uid
var idSet = {};
var rowsByUser = {};
forumRows.forEach(function(row) {
var uid = row.getAttribute('data-last-poster-id');
if (!uid || uid === '' || uid === '0') return;
idSet[uid] = true;
if (!rowsByUser[uid]) rowsByUser[uid] = [];
rowsByUser[uid].push(row);
});

var ids = Object.keys(idSet);
if (!ids.length) {
console.warn('[Panel3] No poster IDs found on forum rows');
return;
}

// Helper: render image into panel-3
function renderPanel3(panel3, imgUrl) {
if (!imgUrl || panel3.querySelector('.fr-o3')) return false;
var frO3 = document.createElement('div');
frO3.className = 'fr-o3';
frO3.style.backgroundImage = "url('" + imgUrl + "')";
panel3.appendChild(frO3);
var frP3 = document.createElement('div');
frP3.className = 'fr-p3';
panel3.appendChild(frP3);
return true;
}

if (typeof WatcherAPI === 'undefined') {
console.warn('[Panel3] WatcherAPI not available, skipping');
return;
}

var PANEL3_FALLBACK = 'https://placehold.co/150x200/1a1a1a/666?text=?';

WatcherAPI.getFields(ids, ['portrait_image', 'rectangle_gif', 'square_image', 'secondary_square_image']).then(function(data) {
var rendered = 0;
forumRows.forEach(function(forumRow) {
var uid = forumRow.getAttribute('data-last-poster-id');
var panel3 = forumRow.querySelector('.panel-3');
if (!uid || !panel3) return;

var fields = data[uid] || {};
var bgImage = fields.portrait_image || fields.rectangle_gif || fields.square_image || fields.secondary_square_image || PANEL3_FALLBACK;
if (renderPanel3(panel3, bgImage)) rendered++;
});
console.log('[Panel3] Rendered ' + rendered + '/' + forumRows.length + ' portraits');
}).catch(function(err) {
console.error('[Panel3] API error:', err);
});
});
</script>
